surveyProject.title: Perceived Effective of App through logo colors

question.lead:
Dear participant,
thanks for clicking the link to our survey.

As part of our seminar "Fundamentals of Experimental Design and Consumer Behavior" at Leuphana University in Lneburg we are conducting research on the perception of meditation apps.

The survey will take less than 5 minutes. Your data will be anonymized and processed in an aggregated form. Your participation in the survey is voluntary. You can cancel your participation at any moment by clicking the button "Leave and delete my data".

item.text: I hereby confirm that my data may be processed anonymously and in aggregated form. I am aware that no conclusions can be drawn about my person and that I am participating in the study voluntarily and can cancel it at any time.

question.lead:
What is the goal of the survey?

We are a startup developing a meditation app, called "Lotus". Our app is supposed to help its users to relax in everyday life. We plan to upload our app to the AppStore, so people can download it worldwide. For that, we want to know how you perceive our meditation app.

What are meditation apps?

Meditation apps help their users to relax in everyday life by giving guidance and a certain ambience to the user. Usually meditation apps feature guided breathing exercises, dream journeys, body scans or assistance to fall asleep. All in all, the apps are designed to help their users achieve greater ease, relaxation and other benefits such as improved cognitive abilities.

Start of the survey

If you choose to continue, you will have time to look at our logo. We ask you to remeber it, as it will not be shown later in the survey. After you've had a look at the logo for 20 seconds, the "Next" button will come up, so you can proceed.

Thank you for your participation!

Unfortunately, you can't take part in the survey because of either one of the following reasons:

(1) you're not part of the target group we want to investigate upon.

You can now close the page.
